description:
Get started with Brilliant for free at https://brilliant.org/CSIStarbase/  and get 20% off their annual premium subscription!

In Part 2 of this series we will continue with our investigation into the refurbishments and repairs required to return Starship's launch mount to operational status after each launch. 

In Part 1 we covered Flights 1 through 3. In this episode we will cover flights 4 through 7. There will be a major focus on upgrades to the hold down clamps to prevent them from binding up and destroying the booster after liftoff.

LINK TO PART 1: https://youtu.be/f-a3HGxxHws

By the end, I think you will agree that SpaceX has officially maxed out what is physically possible with version 1 of the Orbital Launch Mount.
